---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - BoardTools"
  description="Privacy Guarantee: BoardTools runs 100% in your local browser sandbox. No user inputs, JSON logs, or sketch codes are ever sent to a server."
>
  <section class="max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-8 animate-fade-in-up">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-slate uppercase">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue">Privacy Policy</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-4xl tracking-tight text-primary mt-1">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Principle Highlight -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-success-accent/10 border border-success-accent rounded-2xl flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
      <div class="text-2xl pt-0.5">🔒</div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-primary">The 100% Browser Execution Guarantee</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed">
          At BoardTools, we believe your data belongs strictly on your machine. This website is compiled as a static stack of HTML, CSS, and client-side Javascript. We do not maintain any data collection backend. No strings, parameters, files, design variables, or canvas states ever cross your network interface.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Sections -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-slate leading-relaxed font-sans">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">1. Data We Do Not Collect</h3>
      <p>
        When you perform calculations (e.g., mortgage parameters, BMI numbers), input test text, format files, run audio tests, or view mobile sensory coordinates:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li><strong>No Server Transmission:</strong> Your variables and input details remain within your browser's local sandbox thread.</li>
        <li><strong>No Server Logs:</strong> Since executions do not hit a server API, no calculation values, input payloads, or parameters are recorded in any remote log.</li>
        <li><strong>No Telemetry Tracking:</strong> We do not deploy active telemetry keyloggers, session video recorders, or coordinate analyzers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">2. Browser Local Storage (`localStorage`)</h3>
      <p>
        To make the user experience convenient, BoardTools utilizes your browser's standard database storage:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li><strong>Whiteboard & Sketches:</strong> Draggable notes, drawn coordinates, and background colors are saved to your local database so they persist if you reload the tab.</li>
        <li><strong>Tool History:</strong> A record of the last four tools you loaded is stored locally to populate the "Quick Jump Back" section on the home page.</li>
        <li><strong>Local Reviews:</strong> Any rating or review submitted on this website is written to your local sandbox so you can inspect your changes instantly.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can clear all local storage variables at any time by running the developer terminal console command `localStorage.clear()` or resetting site cookies in your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">3. Security Sandboxing</h3>
      <p>
        All inputs are treated strictly as unparsed strings. We apply rigorous escaping to variables compiled inside preview tools (e.g. SVG preview fields) to prevent cross-site scripting (XSS) issues in your browser runtime.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">4. Cookies and Advertising</h3>
      <p>
        BoardTools does not set tracking cookies, cookie ID tokens, or target marketing pixels. We do not display dynamic network advertisements, and do not track your user profile across the web.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">5. Contacting Us</h3>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our offline architecture, you may inspect the open source codebase directly on GitHub or contact us via our simulated form on the <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">Contact Page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
